.SH NAME
SBO::Lib::Download \- Routines for downloading SlackBuild sources.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 1
\&  use SBO::Lib::Download qw/ check_distfiles /;
\&
\&  my ($ret, $exit) = check_distfiles(LOCATION => $loc, NO_DL => $no_dl);
.Ve
.SH SUBROUTINES
.IX Header "SUBROUTINES"
.SS check_distfiles
.IX Subsection "check_distfiles"
.Vb 1
\&  my ($ret, $exit) = check_distfiles(LOCATION => $loc, NO_DL => $no_dl);
.Ve
.PP
\&\f(CWcheck_distfiles()\fR gets the list of downloads from \f(CW$loc\fR. Any previously\-downloaded
files have their checksums verified. Unless there is a \f(CW\*(C`NO_DL\*(C'\fR argument, missing and
unverifiable files are downloaded to md5sum\-designated directories and verified.
Finally, \f(CWprepare_staging()\fR is run on the downloads.
.PP
In case of success, a hash of source files and destinations from \f(CWprepare_staging()\fR is
returned. The subroutine returns empty if the SlackBuild did not contain any downloads.
In case of failure, an error message and an exit code are returned.
.PP
If there is an argument \f(CW\*(C`NO_DL\*(C'\fR, 1 is returned if all sources are verified and 0
otherwise.
.SS check_manual
.IX Subsection "check_manual"
.Vb 1
\&  my $manual_file = check_manual($filename, $info_md5);
.Ve
.PP
\&\f(CWcheck_manual()\fR checks for a file \f(CW$filename\fR with md5sum \f(CW$info_md5\fR in
\&\f(CW\*(C`SBO_HOME/distfiles/manual\*(C'\fR. It returns the path to this file if it exists
and 0 otherwise.
.SS compute_md5sum
.IX Subsection "compute_md5sum"
.Vb 1
\&  my $md5sum = compute_md5sum($file);
.Ve
.PP
\&\f(CWcompute_md5sum()\fR computes and returns the md5sum of the file in \f(CW$file\fR.
.SS get_distfile
.IX Subsection "get_distfile"
.Vb 1
\&  my ($msg, $err) = get_distfile($link, $md5);
.Ve
.PP
\&\f(CWget_distfile()\fR downloads from the URL \f(CW$link\fR with \f(CWwget(1)\fR and compares
the md5sum to \f(CW$md5\fR. The file is saved in an md5sum\-designated directory.
The subroutine returns a message and an error code upon failure, and 1 upon success.
.SS get_filename_from_link
.IX Subsection "get_filename_from_link"
.Vb 1
\&  my $path = get_filename_from_link($link, $md5);
.Ve
.PP
\&\f(CWget_filename_from_link()\fR returns the full path to the file downloaded from
\&\f(CW$link\fR, given its required md5sum, \f(CW$md5\fR.
.SS get_sbo_downloads
.IX Subsection "get_sbo_downloads"
.Vb 1
\&  my %downloads = %{ get_sbo_downloads(LOCATION => $loc) };
.Ve
.PP
\&\f(CWget_sbo_downloads()\fR gets the download links and md5sums for the SlackBuild
in location \f(CW$loc\fR, returning them in a hash reference.
.SS get_hardlink_from_filename
.IX Subsection "get_hardlink_from_filename"
.Vb 1
\&  my $destination = get_hardlink_from_filename($path, $staging);
.Ve
.PP
\&\f(CWget_hardlink_from_filename()\fR, given a source file at \f(CW$path\fR and a location \f(CW$staging\fR,
returns the destination path for linking the file.
.SS prepare_staging
.IX Subsection "prepare_staging"
.Vb 1
\&  my $destinations = prepare_staging({%downloads});
.Ve
.PP
\&\f(CWprepare_staging()\fR prepares a hash of files and their proper names based on
\&\f(CW%downloads\fR for use during the build in a staging directory.
.SS stage
.IX Subsection "stage"
.Vb 1
\&  stage($location, $distfiles);
.Ve
.PP
\&\f(CWstage()\fR takes a location and a hash of distfiles to create the staging directory for
a build; the SlackBuild directory is copied over and hardlinks to the required source
files are created. It returns the location of the staging directory if it can be created
and 0 otherwise.
.PP
The script exits if the \f(CW\*(C`distfiles\*(C'\fR directory is malformed or the source file or directory
is a symlink.
.SS unstage
.IX Subsection "unstage"
.Vb 1
\&  my $res = unstage();
.Ve
.PP
\&\f(CWunstage()\fR is a shorthand subroutine for the removal of the staging directory when building
is complete or upon signal. It has no useful return value.
.SS verify_distfile
.IX Subsection "verify_distfile"
.Vb 1
\&  my $bool = verify_distfile($link, $md5);
.Ve
.PP
\&\f(CWverify_distfile()\fR verifies that the file downloaded from \f(CW$link\fR has an
md5sum equal to \f(CW$md5\fR.
.SH "EXIT CODES"
.IX Header "EXIT CODES"
Download.pm subroutines can return the following exit codes:
.PP
.Vb 6
\&  _ERR_SCRIPT        2   script or module bug
\&  _ERR_MD5SUM        4   download verification failure
\&  _ERR_DOWNLOAD      5   download failure
\&  _ERR_OPENFH        6   failure to open file handles
\&  _ERR_NOINFO        7   missing download information
\&  _ERR_SBO_HOME      17  could not give SBO_HOME valid contents
.Ve
